					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-519962#post-2182848</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-519962/diary-of-a-young-girl#post-2182848</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Wed, 17 Dec 2014 17:02:44 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>pootis spencer here</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1958479</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>I don't know why, but I enjoy a good SCP that can be shown pity for it's actions. Think about it; Builder Bear was contained after it meet the girl. It missed the girl, and it didn't want to hurt anybody. I feel as if it made the first copy because it wanted make a friend. The copy it made got startled and accidentally killed the containment team. The original and -A escaped. The original made Tommy because, well, that's fairly obvious. The original now knew that his clones were dangerous, knowing that it could hurt others. It was scarred that the foundation would find him and lock him away and be mean to him. It knew that it only had one person to look to; the girl. But it knew that it would be impossible to escape. -A, also scarred that it would be hurt, made -C. During the confusion of -C, the original and -B escaped, but left -A behind, knowing it wanted to hurt others. Both of them escaped, finding the girl. After that, the father found it, so -B killed him to stop him from taking them away. The original knew that the girl would be upset, so it did the thing that it promised itself it would never do; it created another friend. The Bear and Tommy are no longer in the site, but -A and -C are. The original knows this , and one day, it will go back to the site, and stop -A and -C.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
